# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: AlfredArc | Scene: UnmarriedGallowCreek
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "She hadn't yet spoken the words, but she could see the pain in his face."
    new "She hadn't yet spoken the words, but she could see the pain in his face."

    old "Why..."
    new "Why..."

    old "He nearly begged."
    new "He nearly begged."

    old "It's not you, Marius...really."
    new "It's not you, Marius...really."

    old "You are kind, and handsome and...anything a girl could wish for in a husband."
    new "You are kind, and handsome and...anything a girl could wish for in a husband."

    old "So what then?!"
    new "So what then?!"

    old "Why reject me?"
    new "Why reject me?"

    old "She saw the hurt in his eyes."
    new "She saw the hurt in his eyes."

    old "It is as I said, Marius...the problem isn't you. It's me."
    new "It is as I said, Marius...the problem isn't you. It's me."

    old "I cannot bring myself to marry...not now...not for a long time."
    new "I cannot bring myself to marry...not now...not for a long time."

    old "The life I had before I came here...it is so much...I have barely begun to grieve it."
    new "The life I had before I came here...it is so much...I have barely begun to grieve it."

    old "Marius stepped forward."
    new "Marius stepped forward."

    old "But I could help you!"
    new "But I could help you!"

    old "Sarah shook her head again."
    new "Sarah shook her head again."

    old "No...I'm sorry, but I will not marry you."
    new "No...I'm sorry, but I will not marry you."

    old "Marius began to pace about, as if looking for an answer that could somehow bring her to change her mind."
    new "Marius began to pace about, as if looking for an answer that could somehow bring her to change her mind."

    old "There was none."
    new "There was none."

    old "But...you...and..."
    new "But...you...and..."

    old "Gods! Again!"
    new "Gods! Again!"

    old "He kicked the dust in the yard, causing it to linger in the air."
    new "He kicked the dust in the yard, causing it to linger in the air."

    old "Without you...I'll..."
    new "Without you...I'll..."

    old "He was at a loss for words."
    new "He was at a loss for words."

    old "He had clearly not expected this answer."
    new "He had clearly not expected this answer."

    old "Listen, Marius..."
    new "Listen, Marius..."

    old "She tried to comfort him, but he flinched from her as if she was a stinging plant."
    new "She tried to comfort him, but he flinched from her as if she was a stinging plant."

    old "Everything I said about you is true...any girl will be lucky to call you their husband."
    new "Everything I said about you is true...any girl will be lucky to call you their husband."

    old "Yeah? Where are they then!?"
    new "Yeah? Where are they then!?"

    old "This blasted town is scarce any unwed woman, and certainly none that will take a chance on a man of my prospects!"
    new "This blasted town is scarce any unwed woman, and certainly none that will take a chance on a man of my prospects!"

    old "Curses!"
    new "Curses!"

    old "He yelled out again, his voice carrying across the fields."
    new "He yelled out again, his voice carrying across the fields."

    old "Enough! I don't want to hear any of your excuses."
    new "Enough! I don't want to hear any of your excuses."

    old "Clearly, you have no interest in me."
    new "Clearly, you have no interest in me."

    old "Marius, I didn't-"
    new "Marius, I didn't-"

    old "No, we can be honest now. No more pretending."
    new "No, we can be honest now. No more pretending."

    old "He looked over at the house."
    new "He looked over at the house."

    old "I think...you can stay the night, but after that it is probably best that you take leave."
    new "I think...you can stay the night, but after that it is probably best that you take leave."

    old "Sarah felt her heart tremble."
    new "Sarah felt her heart tremble."

    old "She knew he might take it poorly, but had not expected he would actually throw her out."
    new "She knew he might take it poorly, but had not expected he would actually throw her out."

    old "Your presence in our house has been a distraction. It is time my father and I get back to our regular lives."
    new "Your presence in our house has been a distraction. It is time my father and I get back to our regular lives."

    old "And with the harvest season soon ending, we won't need your housekeeping services any more."
    new "And with the harvest season soon ending, we won't need your housekeeping services any more."

    old "Services, as if she had been but a maid to them."
    new "Services, as if she had been but a maid to them."

    old "Sarah straightened out her back and stared Marius down."
    new "Sarah straightened out her back and stared Marius down."

    old "Now she saw him."
    new "Now she saw him."

    old "The small man. The petty man."
    new "The small man. The petty man."

    old "Kind when he figured he could get what he wanted from her. Cruel when she had no more use of him."
    new "Kind when he figured he could get what he wanted from her. Cruel when she had no more use of him."

    old "The father and the son, both loathsome in their own way."
    new "The father and the son, both loathsome in their own way."

    old "By next morning, I will take leave of your house."
    new "By next morning, I will take leave of your house."

    old "He almost spat out the word."
    new "He almost spat out the word."

    old "With that, it was over."
    new "With that, it was over."

    old "She returned to the house to sleep, though she slept poorly that last night."
    new "She returned to the house to sleep, though she slept poorly that last night."

    old "When she woke the next morning, Marius had already informed his father that Sarah was leaving."
    new "When she woke the next morning, Marius had already informed his father that Sarah was leaving."

    old "Alfred made a motion to keep her, but Sarah knew the father was even more lecherous than the son."
    new "Alfred made a motion to keep her, but Sarah knew the father was even more lecherous than the son."

    old "She refused, and as promised, gathered her scarce belongings and set out on the road again."
    new "She refused, and as promised, gathered her scarce belongings and set out on the road again."

    old "The town of Gallow's Creek was small, and in little time at all, she left it far behind her."
    new "The town of Gallow's Creek was small, and in little time at all, she left it far behind her."

    old "In the rest of her life, the time spend at Gallow's Creek would prove but a passing memory, one of little relevance or impact."
    new "In the rest of her life, the time spend at Gallow's Creek would prove but a passing memory, one of little relevance or impact."

    old "After a few days walking she reached the nearby city."
    new "After a few days walking she reached the nearby city."

    old "Sarah did not have a coin to her name, so sold the only thing of value that she had, the dress she had worn when she fled Rosanna."
    new "Sarah did not have a coin to her name, so sold the only thing of value that she had, the dress she had worn when she fled Rosanna."

    old "Delicate in craftsmanship and material, it fetched her a good amount, though far less than it was worth."
    new "Delicate in craftsmanship and material, it fetched her a good amount, though far less than it was worth."

    old "The coin from selling her dress lasted her a few months, enough for bread and a place to stay as she moved from inn to inn."
    new "The coin from selling her dress lasted her a few months, enough for bread and a place to stay as she moved from inn to inn."

    old "From city to city."
    new "From city to city."

    old "The money would never last, so Sarah took to working."
    new "The money would never last, so Sarah took to working."

    old "She knew how to clean and cook a little, enough to be paid for it."
    new "She knew how to clean and cook a little, enough to be paid for it."

    old "She could read and write, making her popular with the wealthier families in the city's she stayed in."
    new "She could read and write, making her popular with the wealthier families in the city's she stayed in."

    old "Sarah would be their cook, their maid, or help raise their children."
    new "Sarah would be their cook, their maid, or help raise their children."

    old "Always for just a few months, before she'd vanish onto the next."
    new "Always for just a few months, before she'd vanish onto the next."

    old "No place ever felt like home."
    new "No place ever felt like home."

    old "And some unfamiliar force called on her to keep wandering."
    new "And some unfamiliar force called on her to keep wandering."

    old "Along the way, her life was filled with an endless flood of new faces and names."
    new "Along the way, her life was filled with an endless flood of new faces and names."

    old "Fellow travelers, friends she'd make, employers."
    new "Fellow travelers, friends she'd make, employers."

    old "An occasional lover."
    new "An occasional lover."

    old "But she was forever detached from the world, and the people faded away just as the places did."
    new "But she was forever detached from the world, and the people faded away just as the places did."

    old "More than two decades had passed since she had left the town of Gallow's Creek, by now less than a memory."
    new "More than two decades had passed since she had left the town of Gallow's Creek, by now less than a memory."

    old "Sarah sat beneath the shade of a large tree, taking respite with fellow travelers as she neared a new city."
    new "Sarah sat beneath the shade of a large tree, taking respite with fellow travelers as she neared a new city."

    old "Another woman, two decades younger than her, sat besides her."
    new "Another woman, two decades younger than her, sat besides her."

    old "Young woman\" \"Headed to town for work too?"
    new "Young woman\" \"Headed to town for work too?"

    old "Young woman\" \"They says jobs plenty, good pay too."
    new "Young woman\" \"They says jobs plenty, good pay too."

    old "They always say that, don't they?"
    new "They always say that, don't they?"

    old "The young woman laughed."
    new "The young woman laughed."

    old "Young woman\" \"Ay, maybe. I ain't been around as long as you though."
    new "Young woman\" \"Ay, maybe. I ain't been around as long as you though."

    old "You calling me old?"
    new "You calling me old?"

    old "Young woman\" \"Sorry, I didn't mean no disrespect."
    new "Young woman\" \"Sorry, I didn't mean no disrespect."

    old "Sarah waved her hand, dismissing the girl's concern."
    new "Sarah waved her hand, dismissing the girl's concern."

    old "Don't worry about it. No offense taken."
    new "Don't worry about it. No offense taken."

    old "The young woman leaned in closer."
    new "The young woman leaned in closer."

    old "Young woman\" \"I worked down south in a laundry crew till they fired people cause of end o season."
    new "Young woman\" \"I worked down south in a laundry crew till they fired people cause of end o season."

    old "Young woman\" \"By what ways you comin from?"
    new "Young woman\" \"By what ways you comin from?"

    old "Sarah smiled as she looked at the road, stretching ever on."
    new "Sarah smiled as she looked at the road, stretching ever on."

    old "Oh, I used to be a princess."
    new "Oh, I used to be a princess."

    old "But it's been a long road since."
    new "But it's been a long road since."

    old "Princess to refugee. Refugee to vagrant. Wanderer."
    new "Princess to refugee. Refugee to vagrant. Wanderer."

